    Hdf5 Compression Investigation¶

    One of the benefits of the yaml interface is the possibility for generating the yaml automatically. This was particularly useful when evaluating the compression algorithms that come with HDf5 and HDF5-rust. In this example we generate an exhaustive combination of compression options and visualize how they affect the processing time and the hdf5 compression.

    Given that there are so many combinations, it was practical to use a very small file for this investigation. The input tpx3 file was 1.1Mb. Below you can see the impact of each of the variables on the file size and processing performance.

    Note

    The below data is representative of a very small raw data size (1.1Mb) due to the practicalities of so many luna runs. You may base your decision on which algorithm and parameters to use on this data, but keep in mind that at this time we do not know if the performance scales as we expect.

    In short, it might be a good idea to use this script and find out for yourself which compression sets are right for your data.

    Python Script¶

    noindex:

    Automate generation of yaml file¶
      1import os
  2from io import StringIO
  3
  4from ruamel.yaml import YAML
  5from ruamel.yaml.comments import CommentedMap
  6import pandas as pd
  7import seaborn as sns
  8import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
  9import sys
 10
 11import warnings
 12warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=FutureWarning)
 13
 14sys.path.append(os.path.abspath(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), '..')))
 15from env_vars_for_docs_examples import COMPRESSION_DATA_FNAME, PYTHON_EXAMPLE_OUTPUT_DIR, PLOTS_DIRECTORY
 16
 17
 18def generate_compression_analysis_yaml():
 19    algo = [
 20        None,
 21        "BloscLz4hc",
 22        "BloscBlosclz",
 23        "BloscSnappy",
 24        "BloscZlib",
 25        "BloscLz4",
 26        "Deflate",
 27        "BloscZstd"
 28    ]
 29    shuffle = [None, "Bit", "Byte"]
 30    level = [None, 1, 5, 9]
 31    nthreads = [1, 12, 24]
 32    chunk_size = [2 ** 10, 2 ** 12, 2 ** 14, 2 ** 15]
 33
 34    # 1MB
 35    raw_data_path = "$(ASI_TEST_SUITE)/Tpx3/02_Intensified_TPX3CAM/01_with_gamma_scintillator/space_test/int_contmun5min_withCshutterclose000001.tpx3"
 36    layout = "Tpx3Single"
 37
 38    base_yaml = {
 39        'timepixSchemaVersion': '1.0.0',
 40        'datasets': [
 41            {
 42                "id": "BaseYaml",
 43                'layout': layout,
 44                'detectorType': 'Tpx3',
 45                'description': 'None',
 46                'application': 'VMI',
 47                'data': [
 48                    {'path': raw_data_path}
 49                ],
 50                'analysis': []
 51            }
 52        ]
 53    }
 54
 55    analysis_template = {
 56        'epsSpace': 1,
 57        'epsTime': "150ns",
 58        'timeBinInterval': "1s",
 59        'numTimeBins': 5,
 60        'rawOnly': False,
 61        'logLevel': "info"
 62    }
 63
 64    for a in algo:
 65        for s in shuffle:
 66            for n in nthreads:
 67                for l in level:
 68                    for c in chunk_size:
 69                        analysis_id = f"Algorithm_{a}_Shuffle_{s}_nThreads_{n}_CompressionLevel_{l}_Hdf5ChunkSize_{c}"
 70                        output_file = f"{raw_data_path.replace('.tpx3', '')}_{analysis_id}.h5"
 71                        analysis_entry = {
 72                            'id': analysis_id,
 73                            'outputFile': output_file,
 74                            'compressionAlgorithm': a,
 75                            'compressionShuffle': s,
 76                            'compressionNthreads': n,
 77                            'compressionLevel': l,
 78                            "hdf5ChunkSize": c,
 79                        }
 80                        analysis_entry.update(analysis_template)
 81                        base_yaml['datasets'][0]['analysis'].append(analysis_entry)
 82    yaml = YAML()
 83    yaml.default_flow_style = False
 84    stream = StringIO()
 85    yaml.dump(base_yaml, stream)
 86    yaml_string = stream.getvalue()
 87    return yaml_string
 88
 89
 90def convert_to_seconds(time_str):
 91    if 'ms' in time_str:
 92        return float(time_str.replace('ms', '')) / 1000
 93    elif 's' in time_str:
 94        return float(time_str.replace('s', ''))
 95    else:
 96        return float(time_str)
 97
 98
 99def plot():
100    df = pd.read_csv(COMPRESSION_DATA_FNAME)
101    df['graph_execution_time'] = df['graph_execution_time'].apply(convert_to_seconds)
102    for hue in ["compression_algorithm", "compression_nthreads", "compression_shuffle", "compression_level",
103                "hdf5_chunk_size"]:
104        # Plot for compression algorithm
105        fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 6))
106        sns.barplot(
107            x='compression_algorithm', y='graph_execution_time',
108            hue=hue, data=df, ax=axes[0],
109            edgecolor="black", linewidth=1
110        )
111        axes[0].set_xlabel('Compression Algorithm')
112        axes[0].set_ylabel('Processing Time (seconds)')
113        axes[0].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
114
115        sns.barplot(
116            x='compression_algorithm', y='filesize_in_megabytes',
117            hue=hue, data=df, ax=axes[1],
118            edgecolor="black", linewidth=1
119        )
120        axes[1].set_xlabel('Compression Algorithm')
121        axes[1].set_ylabel('File Size (MB)')
122        axes[1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
123        sns.despine(fig)
124
125        plt.suptitle("Evaluation of compression on performance. \n(Input .tpx3 file 1MB)")
126
127        fig_fname = os.path.join(PLOTS_DIRECTORY, f"evaluation_compression_algorithms_{hue}.png")
128        fig.savefig(fig_fname, bbox_inches="tight", dpi=250)
129        print(f"Figure saved to \"{fig_fname}\"")
130
131
132if __name__ == "__main__":
133    yaml_string = generate_compression_analysis_yaml()
134    print(yaml_string)
135    plot()
